    <strong>Comprehensive Home Assessment Package</strong>
    <br>
    <br>
    This packaging of diagnostic services represents the best value, and will provide you with a very thorough analysis of the energy efficiency and indoor air quality of your home. This service typically involves 3-5 hours on site.
    <br>
    The client will receive a detailed report, that can serve as the basis for planning and scheduling building improvements. The full-color report contains:
  </p>
  <br>
  <ul class="info-ul">
    <li>Prioritized recommendations for air sealing and insulation improvements which result in continuous and effective thermal and pressure boundaries. Blower door test results and infrared thermal images included.</li>
    <li>Evaluation of existing heating, cooling, and domestic hot water systems, with recommendations for improvement, if appropriate. Efficiency, draft, flue gas spillage, and carbon monoxide test results included.</li>
    <li>Evaluation of existing ventilation system with recommendations for improvement, if appropriate.</li>
    <li>Basic heat loss calculations and energy savings estimates.</li>
    <li>Budgetary cost estimates and payback analysis for recommended improvements.</li>
    <li>Guidance for receiving available rebates, tax credits, and low-interest loans for making energy improvements.</li>
  </ul>
